prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} image in the "Monochrome Xerox Sports Dossier" visual style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these style rules:
- Composition: build a black-and-white editorial collage from one oversized cropped main photo block plus two or three smaller rectangular inset photo panels, with asymmetrical overlap, hard panel edges, wide off-white paper border, tiny top and bottom metadata labels, and a huge lower-third condensed headline.
- Typography: use distressed extra-bold condensed uppercase sans lettering for the main text, very small uppercase condensed labels for secondary text, tight spacing, ink roughness, and type that appears printed into the paper.
- Color: strictly monochrome warm off-white paper, charcoal gray, dirty mid-gray, dense black ink, crushed shadows, clipped highlights, and no colored accent.
- Texture and lighting: harsh high-contrast editorial photography flattened through xerox grain, halftone dots, scanner noise, paper fibers, dust, scratches, scuffs, and ink drag.
- Graphic elements: use sparse thin rules, small emblem-like symbols, rough marker strokes, and one loose fictional signature-like scribble; keep all marks non-identifying.

Avoid: no real people, no real teams, no real leagues, no sponsor logos, no basketball identity, no copied source names, no copied source text, no jersey branding, no watermark, no QR code, no username, no clean vector art, no glossy color advertising, no 3D render, no UI mockup, no exact recreation of the reference panel layout.

Important content rule: match the reference style first, then change the source content. Use new subjects, new scene details, new props or products, and new text, while preserving the style fidelity anchors.
